  }, "Boss Edge")), mdx("p", null, "A boss is a force to be reckoned with, and as such, it is more powerful in a number of ways. A boss cannot be subject to a finishing blow unless its hit point total has been reduced to zero. Furthermore, a boss NPC gets advantage on all attack rolls equal to its boss edge score."), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("h5", {
